      "status": "done",
      "title": "Improve or explicitly constrain image follow-up behavior",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "images",
        "multimodal",
        "ux"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "src/context.ts",
        "test/context.test.ts",
        "README.md",
        "docs/cursor-model-ux-spec.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "src/context.ts:21-37 forwards images only from the latest user message.",
        "src/context.ts:39-48 replaces historical images with [image omitted from transcript].",
        "docs/cursor-model-ux-spec.md:15-16 records this as a pending product decision."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Choose a policy: keep current behavior with explicit prompt limitation, or add opt-in recent-image carry-forward with token/privacy budget.",
        "Implement the chosen behavior and update tests.",
        "Update README/spec so users understand multimodal follow-up semantics.",
        "Run npm test and npm run typecheck."
      ],
      "notes": [
        "Started by agent to clarify image follow-up behavior.",
        "Chose explicit-constraining policy for multimodal follow-ups. Added prompt boundary that only latest-user images are available as bytes and Cursor should ask for reattachment/description for prior images. Updated context tests, README, and UX spec. Validated with npm test -- test/context.test.ts, npm test, npm run typecheck. Reviewer subagent reported no material findings."
      ],
